# Vault Routing

Folder numbering follows decade logic:
- 00-09 → Time (daily notes, inbox)
- 10-19 → Thinking (ideation, problem framing)
- 20-29 → Reference (reusable LLM context blocks)
- 30-39 → Execution (initiative specs)
- 40-49 → People (direct reports, stakeholders)
- 50-59 → Business (services, catalog, customers)
- 60-69 → Records (decisions)
- 70-79 → Delegation (delegation briefs)
- 80-89 → Sessions (LLM re-anchors)
- 90-99 → Comms (meeting notes)
- _     → System (templates, prompts, attachments)

## Routing Table

| What it is | Where it lives |
|---|---|
| Today's plan, schedule, carry-over tasks | vault/00-daily/ |
| Raw capture, unprocessed thought | vault/01-inbox/ |
| Half-formed idea, problem framing | vault/10-thinking/ |
| API reference (auth, endpoints, gotchas) | vault/20-context/apis/ |
| Data structure definition (fields, types) | vault/20-context/schemas/ |
| Reusable approach (code or process pattern) | vault/20-context/patterns/ |
| Business model, OSOM, org context, glossary | vault/20-context/business/ |
| Active initiative (spec, status, delegation) | vault/30-initiatives/ |
| Person note, 1:1 log, capability map | vault/40-people/ |
| OSOM service unit (internal delivery, P&L) | vault/50-services/ |
| External product or service offering | vault/51-catalog/ |
| Customer account, segment, relationship | vault/52-customers/ |
| Decision record (what, why, what was rejected) | vault/60-decisions/ |
| Delegation brief (outcome, authority, level) | vault/70-delegation/ |
| LLM session re-anchor (state, next steps) | vault/80-sessions/ |
| Meeting notes | vault/90-meeting-notes/ |
| Note templates (Templater syntax) | vault/_templates/ |
| Prompt templates (LLM prompt structures) | vault/_prompts/ |

## Key Distinctions — Easy to Confuse

**50-services vs 51-catalog**
- 50-services = HOW we operate internally (service managers, P&L, OSOM units)
- 51-catalog  = WHAT we sell externally (products, tiers, offerings)

**20-context vs 30-initiatives**
- 20-context    = reusable reference, injected into many LLM sessions
- 30-initiatives = one initiative's context, specific to that project

**60-decisions vs 30-initiatives**
- Decisions live in 60-decisions/
- Initiative notes LINK TO decisions — they don't store them

**70-delegation vs 40-people**
- Delegation brief lives in 70-delegation/
- Person note in 40-people/ links to it and tracks status

## Rules

- Read ABOUT.md in any folder before assuming what belongs there
- If a request could go in two places — ask before creating
- Never create files in vault/_attachments/ — Obsidian manages that folder
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones when content clearly belongs there
